news.title: Nielsen Media, group company leases over 1.52 lakh sq ft in Mumbai's Goregaon
news.para: Of the total office space, Nielsen Media will occupy the 36th to 38th floors, while What’s On Media, a group company of Nielsen Media, will take up the 35th floor of the tower.

news.title: New home prices in China fall by 4.5% in June 2024
news.para: New home prices were down 4.5% from a year earlier, hitting the lowest since June 2015, deeper than a 3.9% slide in May, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data.

news.title: Asking prices for home in UK falls by 0.4% in June 2024: Rightmove
news.para: The company said the average asking price was 373,493 pounds ($484,943) for property put on sale between June 9 to July 6, 0.4% less than a month earlier.

news.title: Jammu Smart City plans to construct green buildings along Tawi riverfront
news.para: The project also aims to make recreational, residential, commercial, and green spaces on the reclaimed land and the adjoining warehouse.

news.title: Hindalco to sell land parcel to Ekamaya Properties for Rs 595 crore
news.para: The transaction is subject to signing of definitive documents, completion of customary closing conditions and receipt of regulatory approvals, it said.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP set to hold survey of houses in Sushant Lok
news.para: The residents’ welfare association (RWA) of the sectors wrote to DTCP last week, seeking action against illegal construction. Residents said most of the newly constructeded buildings in the colony have been built in violation of the plans sanctioned by DTCP.

news.title: Nagpur: Indora metro station’s opening delayed again
news.para: A senior metro official said that although the station is almost complete, with only the final touches remaining, it cannot start operating without the mandatory approval from the Commissioner of Metro Rail Safety (CMRS).

news.title: Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout allottees miffed with poor state of amenities
news.para: Nagendra (name changed), a resident of 5th Block, F Sector, NPKL, said, “Two or three days of rain has ruined our lives. We’re unable to come out of our homes.

news.title: Sebi to auction 19 properties of seven companies on August 12
news.para: Sunheaven Agro India, Ravi Kiran Realty India Ltd, Jivan Sathi Dream Projects and Purusattam Infotech Industries are the other companies whose properties will be auctioned by the markets watchdog.

news.title: Average time to complete large residential projects dip 20% in last decade
news.para: For all large projects launched and completed between 2014 and H1 2024, the average completion time was lowest in Chennai with 3.6 years, while Hyderabad and Bangalore clocked in at 4.2 and 4.8 years respectively.

news.title: Flat buyers in Karnataka dread losing plots, want law to gain ownership
news.para: The Bangalore Apartments Federation (BAF) recently appealed to deputy chief minister DK Shivakumar that the govt expedite its measures to update the laws.

news.title: NCLT dismisses resolution for Rajesh Lifespaces' hotels business, orders rerun
news.para: The corporate insolvency resolution process (CIRP) of Rajesh Business & Leisure Hotels, managed by the resolution professional (RP), had witnessed competing proposals from consortiums led by Sankalp Consortium and Rare ARC-Shree Naman Developers.

news.title: Plot owners in Noida protest as they await possession even eight years after registry
news.para: Noida Authority officials could not be contacted for their comments, "We're fed up with the Noida Authority's endless excuses and lack of transparency," said Latsahab Lohia, president of Sector 145 RWA.

news.title: Four people booked for cheating Navi Mumbai builder of Rs 66.75 lakh in land deal
news.para: They also fabricated documents of various agreements, transfer orders of the City and Industrial Development Corporation (CIDCO) and gained the confidence of the victim hailing from Sanpada, the official from CBD police station said quoting a complaint.

news.title: Karnataka accelerate efforts to establish sector-specific clusters in various cities
news.para: The govt’s efforts have seen initial success with 300 companies setting up offices in smaller cities, creating 3,000 jobs. Kharge emphasized the need to change the perception that Karnataka is solely associated with Bengaluru.

news.title: L&DO clears 15 acre land in eviction drive in Delhi’s Civil Lines
news.para: Sources said the current market value of the large patch of around 32 acres, including the cleared portion, in the area is estimated at over Rs 2,000 crore.

news.title: Telangana: About 12,000 buildings derails Musi beautification project
news.para: The structures, including big apartment complexes, gated communities and independent houses, have come up within the 50-metre buffer zone on either side of the Musi over the decades and the govt has its task cut out in pulling down these encroachments.

news.title: NBCC interested in taking over all of Supertech's pending projects
news.para: During the insolvency proceedings of one of the group companies of Supertech, the interim resolution professional (IRP) had approached NBCC.

news.title: Macrotech Developers reports 20% growth in sales bookings in Q1 FY25
news.para: As per its latest operational update posted on stock exchanges, the collection from customers rose 12 per cent to Rs 2,690 crore in April-June FY25 from Rs 2,400 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Institutional investors infuse $637.9 million in Indian real estate in Q1 FY25
news.para: As per the data, institutional investments in the Indian real estate rose 96 per cent in April-June to USD 3.1 billion from USD 1.6 billion in the corresponding period of the previous year.
